The White House has released a statement on the parliamentary elections in Japan, which took place on August 30, 2009. The statement emphasizes the historic nature of the election in one of the world's leading democracies. The United States, being a close friend and ally of Japan, expresses confidence in the formation of a new Japanese government. The statement also highlights the expectation that the strong U.S.-Japan Alliance and partnership between the two countries will continue to thrive under the leadership of the next government in Tokyo. President Obama is looking forward to working closely with the new Japanese Prime Minister on various global, regional, and bilateral issues.